I almost enjoy reading more about books than reading the books themselves. The history, the mindset, the literary context… all of the metadata is fascinating. Nothing is too inside-baseball for me. I want to read everything.

Google Reader was special because it let you mark everything as unread and you could work your way through it. Replacements don’t… is the perception that content expires?

First of all, content is evergreen. Sometimes it is more timely, but there might be a reason to read from the beginning of something.

How many clicks will it take to mark everything as unread? If you are me, you will do this.

What could a mark unread reader look like? Let’s call it evergreen.
